    graph.packing
    Optimization package that obtains near-optimal solution to the 1- and 2-packing combinatorial optimization problem.
    parallel.distributed
    Extends the basic functionality found in the parallel package over many remote JVMs distributed over a network of machines.

    popt4jlib: a parallel optimization library for Java.

    • Uses of SubjectIntf in popt4jlib

      Classes in popt4jlib that implement SubjectIntf 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  GLockingObservableObserverBase
      base class implementing both the SubjectIntf and ObserverIntf interfaces with all implemented methods locking on the global "popt4jlib" w-lock.
      Methods in popt4jlib with parameters of type SubjectIntf 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      private void GLockingObservableObserverBase.addSubjectIncumbent(SubjectIntf subject, java.lang.Object soln)
      add the soln into a hash-map maintaining (SubjectIntf, Object soln) pairs.
      void GLockingObservableObserverBase.notifyChange(SubjectIntf subject)
      when a subject's thread calls the method notifyChange, in response, this object will add the best solution found by the subject, in the _subjects' solutions map, to be later picked up by the first optimizer Thread spawned by this object.
      void GLockingObserverBase.notifyChange(SubjectIntf subject)
      when a subject's thread calls the method notifyChange, in response, this object will invoke the sub-class's implementation of the abstract notifyChangeProtected(subject) method (template method style).
      void ObserverIntf.notifyChange(SubjectIntf subject)
      called by a subject monitored when it changes its state.
      protected abstract void GLockingObserverBase.notifyChangeProtected(SubjectIntf subject)
      sub-classes must implement this method to actually act on the notification.

    • Uses of SubjectIntf in popt4jlib.BH

      Classes in popt4jlib.BH that implement SubjectIntf 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  DGABH
      A parallel/distributed implementation of the Generalized Adaptive Basin Hopping algorithm, using an island-model of computation, where multiple populations are evolved in separate "islands", exchanging individuals in the same migration model as in DGA and DPSO classes.

    • Uses of SubjectIntf in popt4jlib.GA

      Classes in popt4jlib.GA that implement SubjectIntf 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  DGA
      The DGA class implements a thread-safe parallel Distributed Genetic Algorithm that follows the island-model of GA computation, with an elitist selection strategy that uses roulette-wheel selection of individuals based on their fitness (that is computed every generation).

    • Uses of SubjectIntf in popt4jlib.GradientDescent

      Methods in popt4jlib.GradientDescent with parameters of type SubjectIntf 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      protected void AlternatingVariablesDescent.notifyChangeProtected(SubjectIntf subject)
      when a subject's thread calls the method notifyChange, in response, this object will call its minimize() method, and add the result back into the subject object.
      protected void ArmijoSteepestDescentST.notifyChangeProtected(SubjectIntf subject)
      when a subject's thread calls the method notifyChange, in response, this object will call its minimize() method, and add the result back into the subject object.
      protected void FletcherConjugateGradientST.notifyChangeProtected(SubjectIntf subject)
      when a subject's thread calls the method notifyChange, in response, this object will add the best solution found by the subject, in the _observers' solutions map.
      protected void PolakRibiereConjugateGradientST.notifyChangeProtected(SubjectIntf subject)
      when a subject's thread calls the method notifyChange, in response, this object will set the best solution found by the subject, as the initial point to start the PRCG optimization process, and upon completion of the optimization process, it will add back the new solution to the subject by calling the subject's addIncumbent(this,sol) method.

    • Uses of SubjectIntf in popt4jlib.PS

      Classes in popt4jlib.PS that implement SubjectIntf 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  DPSO
      A parallel implementation of the Particle Swarm Optimization algorithm for function optimization, implementing also the SubjectIntf and ObserverIntf objects by extending the GLockingObservableObserverBase class, so that it may be combined with other optimization processes and produce better results.

      A parallel implementation of the Firefly Algorithm for function optimization, implementing also the SubjectIntf and ObserverIntf objects by extending GLockingObservableObserverBase so that it may be combined with other optimization processes and produce better results.
